Images of Google’s Pixel Slate tablet have been leaked ahead of the company’s hardware launch event on 9 October 2018. Leaked images of the Pixel Slate were obtained and published by MySmartPrice. According to the report, the Pixel Slate will feature a detachable keyboard accessory, an active stylus, and USB Type-C connectivity. There is a camera on the front and one on the rear of the device, with a small Google logo emblazoned on the rear of the tablet. The leaked image shows an operating system that can run Android apps and includes a dock for quick access applications at the bottom of the tablet’s screen. Google is set to officially launch its Pixel Slate tablet at a special event on 9 October.